Gibson Achonu, Owerri Tragedy befell the family of Ezikeigwe in the Umuezike village, Mbosi, in the Ihiala Local Government Area of Anambra State as five members of the family mysteriously died on Boxing Day. Mr Lawrence Ezikeigwe, 61, who was said to reside in Lagos with his family, reportedly came home on December 23, 2019, for the Christmas celebration, but met his untimely death together with his family members. It was gathered that the couple, who were with two male and one female children, were discovered dead on December 26, 2019, when the door of their residence was broken as they did not wake up on time as expected. Southern City News gathered that the neighbours were worried when people who came to visit the family and met with disappointment and left after knocking at their door several times in the bid to see them. A source close to the family stated that they died from the combustion of carbon monoxide from a power generating set. READ ALSO: Jigawa Rep, Gawo, dies in Dubai, burial holds Thursday “The generator exhaust faced directly to one of the windows kept ajar into the living room, which was kept on till the wee hours of the night. It was on till the fuel in it finished around after 3.17am”, the source stated. The source added that the remains of the deceased had been deposited in an undisclosed mortuary. When contacted, the Anambra Sate Police Public Relations Officer, Haruna Mohammed, said he had yet to confirm the story. “I am not aware of the ugly incident. I will call the DPO of the area to confirm the incident said to have happened at Mbosi in the Ihiala Local Government Area of the state.” Copyright PUNCH.
